# API Keys

a) API acts as a form of authentication, which can lead to access control.
For companies which make money from selling such services, its also a way of tracking.
By blocking a key you can prevent abuse in the case of too-high request volumes.

b) Which benefits do they provide?
- access control
- request volumes control
- authentication

c) Which problems do they generate?
- must be submitted alongside of the web service or requests (to identify the origin of the request)
- has to be verified to prevent tempering with the values